node.text:
Some of my go-tos! Enjoy 😊 

Greek Inspired Salad Jar
* 1-2 cups kale
* 1 tbsp feta cheese
* 4oz chicken thighs 
* 10 olives 
* ¼ cup red onion 
* ½ orange bell pepper 
* ½ cup chickpeas
* 1 tbsp balsamic

BLT Remix Salad jar 
* 1 cup mixed greens
* 2 pieces nitrate free bacon
* 2 eggs 
* ½ cup cucumber 
* 1 cup tomatoes 
* 2 tbsp paleo ranch

Veggie Goddess
* 1 cup mixed greens
* ½ cup red onion 
* ½ cup black beans 
* ½ cup quinoa
* ½ cup cucumber 
* ½ cup tomatoes 
* 1 tbsp balsamic

Tex Mex Jar Combo 
* 1 tbsp cilantro 
* 2 cup lettuce   
* 4oz ground turkey or grass-fed ground beef
* ½ cup corn
* ¼ cup onion 
* ½ cup bell peppers 
* ½ cup tomatoes 
* 1 tbsp balsamic

improves gum health &

Step 3: Brush your teeth normally after and floss like you normally would.

Cheers to great oral health!
Xoxo
Amanda

node.text:
Chia seed pudding 4 ways! ⁠⠀⁠⁠
⁠⠀⁠⁠
Not only is chia seed pudding super easy to make (it takes 5-10 minutes to prepare!), but it’s also delicious and great for preparing ahead of time. One of my favorite things about these recipes is that you can make such a wide variety of tasty combinations that are delicious, filling, & very nutritious! That’s why I’m sharing 4 of my favorite combinations with you. ⁠⠀⁠⁠
⁠⠀⁠⁠
What you’ll need for the raspberry mango:⁠⠀⁠⁠
½C mango⁠⠀⁠⁠
2/3c coconut milk⁠⠀⁠⁠
3 tbsp chia seeds⁠⠀⁠⁠
½ tbsp maple syrup⁠⠀⁠⁠
Stevia to taste⁠⠀⁠⁠
¼ C raspberries⁠⠀⁠⁠
1 tsp vanilla extract⁠⠀⁠⁠
⁠⠀⁠⁠
What you’ll need for the pb&j:⁠⠀⁠⁠
3 tbsp chia seeds⁠⠀⁠⁠
⅔ C almond milk⁠⠀⁠⁠
½ tbsp maple syrup⁠⠀⁠⁠
¼ C peanut butter⁠⠀⁠⁠
¼ C mashed berries ⁠⠀⁠⁠
Stevia to taste a⁠⠀⁠⁠
⁠⠀⁠⁠
What you’ll need for the chocolate mocha:⁠⠀⁠⁠
3 tbsps chia seeds⁠⠀⁠⁠
2 tbsp cacao powder (1 if you like it less strong)⁠⠀⁠⁠
½ C cold coffee⁠⠀⁠⁠
⅔ C almond milk⁠⠀⁠⁠
½ tbsp maple syrup⁠⠀⁠⁠
Stevia to taste⁠⠀⁠⁠
⁠⠀⁠⁠
What you’ll need for the banana split:⁠⠀⁠⁠
3 tbsp chia seeds⁠⠀⁠⁠
⅔ C milk⁠⠀⁠⁠
½ banana⁠⠀⁠⁠
2 tbsps chocolate chips⁠⠀⁠⁠
½ tbsp maple syrup⁠⠀⁠⁠
Stevia to taste⁠⠀⁠⁠
⁠⠀⁠⁠
What to do:⁠⠀⁠⁠
1- Mash up raspberries and place in the bottom of a jar if making the pb&j pudding. If making the raspberry mango, blend the mango and vanilla extract. ⁠⠀⁠⁠
2- In a jar, mix the chia seeds, milk, maple syrup, and stevia together (if making chocolate mocha, include cacao powder and cold coffee.).⁠⠀⁠⁠
3- Stir the pudding ingredients together and cover with an airtight lid.⁠⠀⁠⁠
3- Let sit in the fridge overnight.⁠⠀⁠⁠
4- Add in topping of choice and enjoy when ready to eat! ⁠⠀⁠⁠
⁠⠀⁠⁠
Which would you go for?!⁠⠀⁠⁠
Xx⁠⠀⁠⁠
Amanda⁠⠀⁠⁠
⁠⠀⁠⁠

In case you didn’t know, Chris and I launched our new Master Your Health Ebook recently (link in bio to check it out). The feedback from people who purchased the ebook has been amazing ❤️ *Swipe to see more details and what people are saying about it!*⁠⁠
⁠⁠
After over a year and half of diligently working to create a tool that would help you on this health journey, Chris and I are so confident you’re going to love it!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The reason why I’m so excited about this ebook is because we really poured our heart and soul into creating an ebook that would cover all the bases for living an over healthy lifestyle.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The main pillars of the book include:⁠⁠
* Goal setting worksheet⁠⁠
* Nutriton principles & tips⁠⁠
* Healthy food swaps⁠⁠
* Eating out tips⁠⁠
* Food lists⁠⁠
* Printable grocery sheet⁠⁠
* Beginner + Intermediate Workouts⁠⁠
* Workout tutorials⁠⁠
* Post-workout nutrition tips⁠⁠
* 30 delicious recipes including breakfast, lunch, dinner + desserts!⁠⁠
* Recovery tips⁠⁠
* + so much more⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Honestly, I know you’re going to love it and find it extremely helpful. Can’t wait to hear your feedback!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Xoxo,⁠⁠
Amanda⁠⁠

node.text:
Five simple yet delicious Dinner Recipes 🍽 😋*Swipe to see all 5 ideas!*⠀⁠⁠
.⠀⠀⁠⁠
I’m all for easy and healthy simple recipes. Because eating healthy should not only be sustainable but also taste good! ❤️ These recipes all Include plenty of veggies, protein and healthy carbs.⠀⁠⁠
⠀⠀⁠⁠
1️⃣ 420 CALORIES⠀⁠⁠
Super Healthy Spaghetti Bolognese🍝(using zoodles and 1 cup marinara sauce), pasture-raised chicken (6oz) and stir fried mushrooms (1cup) 1.5 tsp olive oil, sea salt & pepper to taste.⠀⁠⁠
⠀⠀⁠⁠
2️⃣ 404 CALORIES⠀⁠⁠
Healthy version of Egg Fried Rice 🍛⠀⁠⁠
How to Make Cauli Rice: Cut up the raw cauliflower head into pieces and place in food blender until it becomes rice like. Add oil & garlic to a pan, then add cauliflower rice, sea salt & pepper and cook until soft. Add desired seasoning or chopped veggies, like peas.⠀⁠⁠
⠀⠀⁠⁠
3️⃣ 484 CALORIES⠀⁠⁠
Fast and delicious Greek 🥗Salad⠀⁠⁠
Chopped 2 mini cucumbers, 1 cup cherry tomatoes, 1/2 cup chickpeas, onion with the oil, 1/4 lemon juice, & salt in a bowl. You can top with olives and 1 grilled chicken thigh. Swap chicken for feta to make this vegetarian, or add both😋⠀⁠⁠
⠀⠀⁠⁠
4️⃣ 395 CALORIES⠀⁠⁠
Salmon Pesto with Healthy Carbs⠀⁠⁠
4oz wild caught salmon grilled with pesto zoodles, with stir fry vegetables (asparagus, 1 cup mushrooms, 1 cup cherry tomatoes, oil, garlic, salt & pepper)⠀⁠⁠
⠀⠀⁠⁠
5️⃣ 469 CALORIES⠀⁠⁠
Eggplant Mozzarella with Grilled Chicken⠀⁠⁠
1 Eggplant, 3 oz Fresh Mozzarella, 2 cups Marinara Sauce, 3 Basil Leaves. Slice eggplant into 1/2” pieces, and season. Lightly grill eggplant and in pan place slices of mozzarella, 2 tbsp marinara, and 1 basil leaf on each piece.⠀⁠⁠
Bake for 10-12 minutes or until cheese is melted. .⠀⁠⁠
.⠀⁠⁠
.⠀⁠⁠

node.text:
Anti-inflammatory Foods (Swipe to see pro-inflammatory foods)⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Whole foods provide an array of beneficial nutrients, vitamins and minerals. Take it a step further and you’ll see there are many foods associated with anti-inflammatory makers. For example, antioxidants and polyphenols found in plant compounds can protect against oxidative stress.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Now remember, it’s what we do most of the time that matters so much more than what we do some of the time. While the food list in the second slide does encourage an inflammatory response, it’s really eating these foods too often that starts to cause issues. So definitely find the right balance for you!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Berries contain antioxidants called anthocyanins. These compounds have anti-inflammatory effects that may reduce your risk of disease.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
There’s a reason guac is extra. Avocados contain an array of beneficial compounds shown to reduce inflammation.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Omega-3s EPA & DHA found in fatty fish has been shown to reduce inflammation.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Swiss chard, kale, Brussels sprouts and asparagus are filled with Vitamin E; a natural antioxidant which has been shown to reduce inflammation.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Turmeric contains a powerful anti-inflammatory compound called curcumin.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Green tea is very high in EGCG which is low to inhibit inflammation.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Boccoli is rich in sulforaphane, an antioxidant that fights inflammation.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Bell peppers and chili peppers are packed with vitamin C and bell peppers contain the antioxidant quercetin.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Over-consuming the foods in slide two has been shown to increase inflammatory responses in the body.⁠⁠
⁠⁠

node.text:
While it’s definitely normal to reach for more comfort food sometimes, I thought I’d share some other ways that help me cope with emotional times 😁(▶️ Swipe to see some of my alternative solutions)⁠⁠
.⁠⁠
Don’t get me wrong, I love my sweets and dessert 😋 While balance looks different for everyone, I’ve definitely found that adding in some of these healthy habits overtime keeps me grounded during stressful events.⁠⁠
.⁠⁠
Things like exercise, gratitude journaling, dancing, calling friends, reading and even spending some time off social media have really helped to minimize my anxiety & stress over time.⁠⁠
.⁠⁠
It’s also a good idea to check in with yourself when reaching for the fridge or pantry cupboard and ask yourself if you’re actually hungry or if it could be some of these other emotions. Additionally, giving yourself some self care time, especially in the morning, could mean the world of difference to your day even if it’s just for 15 minutes.⁠⁠
.⁠⁠
So, I hope you find some time for you in between the chaos & know you definitely deserve to feel your best 😘  and if you just want some damn dessert, go for it 💯😁⁠⁠
.⁠⁠
Xx,⁠⁠
Amanda⁠⁠

Top benefits of collagen 💙 #vitalinfluencer #stayvital⁠⁠
⁠⁠
@vitalproteins and I teamed up to share some of the many benefits of collagen. I’m sure you’ve probably heard of collagen before but today I wanted to spill all the tea.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Collagen is the main protein in the body and represents 30% of all human protein content. Collagen is also a key component of connective tissues found everywhere from your skin to bones to ligaments to joints.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Collagen peptides act as messengers to the cells and trigger the synthesis and reorganization of new collagen fibers, therefore supporting skin, bone and joint tissue structures. Honestly, so many women I know love adding collagen to their day and I can see why!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Curious how to incorporate collagen? I love making shakes or adding it to coffee in the morning.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Vital proteins has a variety of options on their site and include unflavored and flavored options. Hit my link in bio to check out all their awesome products!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Seriously love it. Xoxo,⁠⁠
Amanda

node.text:
Added Sugars Hide in More Foods Than You May Think! (Swipe to see more examples) ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Here’s an illustration of how sugars can really add up in highly processed foods- even foods you may have thought to be healthier or ‘low sugar’. Now there’s nothing wrong with treating yourself to these foods on occasion, but consuming them regularly can really add up.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Two important things to keep track of:⁠⁠
👉 Your total sugar load for the day ⁠⁠
👉 How much added sugar you’re having in a day⁠⁠
⁠⁠
What’s important to note is that not all sugar is bad, however when it’s NOT paired with fiber like that found in fruit, it can lead to a sugar spike and crash. Fruit juice is a good example of something with “no-added sugar” but since the fiber it’s stripped it’s easy to over-consume and often leads to a spike & crash.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Additionally, added sugars can become highly addicting, leading your body to crave more of these foods. That’s why I recommend going for your fav fruit when you feel a sweet tooth coming on. It’s paired with fiber which helps slow the absorption of the sugar into your bloodstream and comes with additional benefits like beneficial vitamins and minerals. Plus, they’re straight up delicious! ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Here are the details of each food and it’s sugar content: ⁠⁠
-’Green’ Juice: contains a whopping 53 grams of sugar and 0 grams of fiber.⁠⁠
-Strawberry Frappuccino: packs in 51g sugar per 16oz serving.⁠⁠
-Orange Juice: one serving contains 31g sugar & no fiber. ⁠⁠
-Standard Cereal w/ Milk: has 28g sugar per bowl. Most cereals contain lots of added sugars, artificial flavors, colors, etc.⁠⁠
-Standard Jelly: contains 24g sugar per 2 tbsps, which is about what the average person uses in one sitting. ⁠⁠
-Baked Beans: one half cup contains 20g sugar! While most people think of beans as being healthy, this type is one you’d certainly want to limit. ⁠⁠
-Flavored Yogurt: each of these flavored yogurts comes with 20g sugar, which is why it’s a good idea to opt for unflavored yogurt and add your own fruit, honey, etc. . ⁠⁠
-Standard Granola Bar: One pack of standard granola bars contains 11g sugar, canola oil, & brown sugar syrup.⁠⁠
#healthyfood #nutrition #healthyeating

node.text:
4 Starbucks Copycat Recipes You’ll Love! (Swipe to see 3 more ideas) ⁠
⁠
While grabbing one of those Starbucks options is great when you’re in a pinch or simply want a treat, they aren’t as nutritious as you may think. That’s why I wanted to share a few ‘dupes’ you can make at home that contain higher quality, minimal ingredients. Plus, this way you can save some money & have leftovers for later!⁠
⁠
What you need for the Pink Drink: ⁠
-½ cup brewed passion tea⁠
-¼ cup coconut milk⁠
-½ cup fresh strawberries⁠
-Stevia to taste ⁠
⁠
What to do:⁠
1- In a blender, combine the passion tea, coconut milk, strawberries & blend until smooth. ⁠
2- Add stevia to taste & blend. ⁠
3- Pour into a tall glass with ice.⁠
⁠
What you need for the Chocolate Almond Espresso:⁠
-1 cup unsweetened almond milk⁠
-1 packet of instant espresso powder or brewed espresso⁠
-1 tbsp cacao powder or cocoa powder⁠
-Stevia to taste (or honey or maple syrup)⁠
⁠
What to do:⁠
1- Heat up the almond milk until it’s simmering.⁠
2- Add in the espresso powder, cacao, & stevia to taste. ⁠
3- Stir for 1-2 minutes & set aside to cool. ⁠
4- Once cool, pour into a glass with ice.⁠
⁠
What you need for the Egg White Cups:⁠
(makes 6-8 cups)⁠
-1 ½  cup egg whites⁠
-½ tbsp avocado oil⁠
-¾  cup roasted peppers ⁠
-1 cup sautéed spinach ⁠
-½ cup shredded Monterey jack cheese ⁠
⁠
What you need for the Bacon Egg Cups:⁠
(makes 6-8 cups)⁠
-7 eggs ⁠
-4 strips bacon, cooked & chopped⁠
-¼ cup cottage cheese ⁠
-½ cup shredded gruyere cheese ⁠
-½ tbsp avocado oil ⁠
⁠
What to do:⁠
1- In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs and avocado oil.⁠
2 (egg white cups) - Add in the roasted peppers, sautéed spinach, & Monterey jack. Whisk until well combined.⁠
2 (bacon egg cups) - Add in the cottage cheese, gruyere, & cooked bacon. Whisk until combined.⁠
3- If using the sous vide method, pour the mixture into egg molds, cover, & set in a pot of 1 inch boiling water. If baking them in a muffin tray, spray the tray with oil & pour the mixture into each tray. ⁠
4- For the sous vide cups, let the molds sit in the covered pot for 10-12 minutes. If baking, bake them for 15-20 minutes at 350 degrees. ⁠
5- Once ready, pop out the egg cups & enjoy!

node.text:
The power of marketing ( ⏩ swipe to see some much better choices)⁠⁠
⁠⁠
It’s crazy how much marketing can shape and mold our opinion of certain brands. Let’s be real - it’s because marketing works!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
However, it is becoming increasingly important that we become conscious consumers and really start to question if brands actually live it up to the stories and claims they put out there.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The marketing thrown at children these days, with highly processed foods especially irritates me. So many boxes covered in cartoons and colorful imagery trying to draw kids in.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The Hawaiian Punch for example is pretty much just water & high fructose corn syrup with food dyes - yikes! Less that 2% is made from real fruit juices yet the company happily displays all the wonderful fruit on the front of the package.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
As for gatorade, the amount of marketing tying that brand in with pro-athletes is unbelievable. Yet, a simple choice like coconut water full of natural electrolytes and natural sugars would be much better than all the filler ingredients added to this drink along with the blue food dye. I’ve also added some more options for athletes in the third graphic.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Water is also such an under appreciated macronutrient but I’m advocating we start putting water back on its pedestal! If you’re looking to add more flavor to your daily water, try incorporating fresh fruits or herbs in your batches of water.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
I hope you found this helpful! Let me know what other brands you’d like me to talk about. Xoxo,⁠⁠
Amanda⁠⁠
